content: Tell me about a belief you revised once you saw it didn't hold up in practice.
What's a small accomplishment that recently gave you quiet satisfaction?
What did you care about as a kid? How does that connect to the way you approach life now?
What's something that turned out as planned—or even better—that you're grateful for?
If you're open to sharing, what's a problem you're methodically working through?
Is there a routine or system that genuinely makes your life work better?
What's a skill or knowledge area you want to develop further?
Describe your ideal well-structured, productive day.
You're having dinner with anyone from history. Whose expertise or experience would you most want to learn from?
Who is someone who taught you something that shaped how you work or think?
What's something you used to be committed to that you've stepped back from?
Right now, what task or responsibility has your focus?
Describe a time when you felt most competent and reliable.
What's an experience that changed how you approach a recurring challenge?
Looking ahead one year, what ability do you want to sharpen?
Tell me about a time someone's dependable help made a real difference.
Is there a decision you're carefully considering?
What's a method you follow that others might overlook?
What's a principle that's reliably guided your choices?
What's one thing you feel is commonly missed about you when people only see your reserved side?
How has your definition of 'doing things right' changed over time?
Can you think of an experience that made you reconsider how you do something?
What's something you're proud of that others might not notice?
When you think about trust, what makes someone worth trusting?
Tell me about a fear you've worked through by taking steady action.
When things feel off, what gets you back to equilibrium?
What's a position you hold that most people haven't considered carefully?
What's been occupying your attention lately?
Think about a mistake. What did it teach you that you now apply regularly?
When you need to truly recharge, how do you restore yourself?
What's something you let go of to stay focused on what matters?
Is there a place that holds personal significance for you?
Let's imagine nothing held you back. What would you build or accomplish?
What's a thought or idea that's been running in the back of your mind?
If you could instantly master one skill, what capability would make you more effective?
How do you handle disagreement with someone you respect?
Have you noticed anything about your own patterns recently?
You're gifted a completely free afternoon. What do you genuinely enjoy doing in your own time?
What's a difficult reality you've had to accept?
What reliably brings you back to a good state?
Is 'home' a place, a person, or a feeling for you? What does stability mean to you?
Can you remember a conversation or exchange that stayed with you?
What's something you keep doing even though it's not your strength?
When was a careful decision that turned out to be the right call?
What's an activity that draws your full concentration when you're doing it?
What's one area of yourself you're still figuring out?
Besides family, what relationship has quietly shaped who you are?
What's a question you wish people would ask you more often—one that would get past the surface?
In what area of your life are you trying to be more consistent?
Do you have a personal practice you value, or one you'd actually maintain long-term?
When you're feeling depleted, what restores you?
Tell me about something you accomplished through steady, sustained effort. Was it worth it?
If you could send a one-sentence message to your younger self, what would it say?
What's something that both motivates and challenges you?
If you could step back into one experience to have it again, which would you choose?
How do you learn to trust someone? What shows you they're reliable?
What's one thing that keeps getting postponed?
What's a stereotype about your generation that you think is totally wrong—or surprisingly right?
What's something you need but rarely mention?
What's a piece of recognition that actually mattered to you?
Imagine a version of your life where you fully trusted your own judgment. What's different?
What are two principles you follow that sometimes conflict?
Is there a gap between your steady exterior and your real uncertainty? (We all have one.)
Do you ever feel like you play a dependable role that isn't the full picture of who you are?
Is there a 'responsible' version of yourself that takes effort to maintain?
Is there something from your past that still bothers you?
What's a past decision you keep turning over?
Tell me about a part of yourself you've tried to keep in check.
Is there a moment in your life you wish you could undo?
What's a feeling that runs beneath your calm that you rarely show?
Can you remember a time when being the reliable one left you feeling alone?
When it comes to the people you're closest to, what would it take for someone to really understand you?
What's a fundamental need you have that's hard to request?
In what situations is the gap between your inner experience and outer manner widest?
Describe what genuine understanding would actually look like for you.
Is there a quiet truth about yourself that you work around rather than face?
Do you have a recurring thought you haven't fully addressed?
What's a belief you hold that you don't usually say?
Is there something you're holding onto that you know should go?
If your intuition could ask you one hard question right now, what do you think it would be?
